# Gemini (Google AI Studio) — SERVER-ONLY for /api/chat (Vercel serverless or Netlify Function).
# Do NOT prefix with VITE_ (browser bundle would expose the key).
#
# Create a key: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey — set in:
#   Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables (Production + Preview), or
#   Netlify → Site → Environment variables.
# Alias also accepted: GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY
#
# Local: use `vercel dev` from the repo root so `/api/chat` is served; plain `vite` does not run serverless routes.
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# Client-side flag: set to "true" to force the AI UI into demo/offline mode without calling /api/chat.
# Useful for previews / screenshots where you don't want to consume API credits.
# VITE_AI_DEMO_MODE=false

# Google Maps Platform (browser): one key can back many enabled APIs — turn each on in Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Library,
# then under Credentials → your key → API restrictions, allow only what this app (or your backend) needs.
#
# Used by this repo today:
#   - Maps JavaScript API (map + drawing + advanced markers)
#   - Geocoding API (reverse-geocode of work-zone centroid)
#   - Places API (place autocomplete / session suggestions in the map search box)
#
# Posted speed near the map crosshair / work zone:
#   - Roads API must be enabled on the key. Calls use same-origin `/roads-api/*` (Vite dev/preview proxy, or vercel.json / netlify.toml in repo).
#   - Google “Speed Limits” often needs an Asset Tracking license; if Google returns nothing, the app falls back to OpenStreetMap maxspeed.
#   - Override base URL only if you proxy Roads yourself: VITE_ROADS_API_BASE=https://your-backend.example.com/roads/v1
#   - Routes API / Directions API / Distance Matrix
#   - Places API (details, autocomplete)
#   - Street View Static API / Street View metadata
#   - Air Quality API / Pollen API (environmental layers — typically REST; consider a backend proxy so the key is not public)
#
# Restrict this key to HTTP referrers (localhost + production origins). VITE_* values ship in the client bundle — never commit real keys.
# Production: add https://trafficcontrolrental.com/* and https://www.trafficcontrolrental.com/* if you use www.
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# Optional: Map ID from Google Cloud → Map Management (vector map). If unset, the app uses DEMO_MAP_ID for local dev (same idea as <gmp-map map-id="DEMO_MAP_ID">).
# VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_MAP_ID=
